   "source": [
    "Embedding_weights = 32641x10 + 10 (biases)  [Each word has its own 10 trainable weights]\n",
    "\n",
    "lstm_weights: LSTM has 4 gates (Forget,input,candidate,output) . Each gate will have: (10x32) + (32x32) + (32). Therefore total 5504\n",
    "\n",
    "Each NN layer of gate has 32 neurons\n",
    "\n",
    "dense_weights = 32x5 + 5"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "21ab0ebc-85a6-4676-bfee-a9285d0b46e9",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**Talking for the whole model:**\n",
    "\n",
    "We have in total 45000 sentences's int representation, thus embedding layer gets (45000,494)\n",
    "\n",
    "Embedding layer gives (45000,494,10)  [Conceptually talking. In actual it is done for sentences separately\n",
    "\n",
    "LSTM gets inputs by batch_size mentioned by user. So, shape is (batch_size,494,10)\n",
    "\n",
    "LSTM gives output (batch_size,32)\n",
    "\n",
    "Output layer gives (batch_size,5)   (i.e, probability of all 5 ratings for [batch_size] number of sentences)\n",
    "\n",
    "(Each row has probability of the 5 probable ratings and then argmax is done on each row to get rating which has most probability)\n",
    "\n",
    "Therefore, y_predictions = np.argmax(prob_predictions,axis=1)"
   ]
  },
  {
